["726.                                  \xa0                     WILLIAM                      WILLMOTT                                                                                                          was indicted for that                                                          he, at the general delivery of the goal of Newgate, holden at the Justice Hall in the Old-Bailey, on the 28th of October, in the 48th year of his Majesty's reign, was tried and convicted of grand larceny, and was sentenced to be transported for the term of fourteen years, and that he afterwards on 14th of July                      last at the \xa0parish of St. Paul, Shadwell                                                               , was at large before the expiration of the term of fourteen years            .", 'To this indictment the prisoner pleaded', '                                                                           GUILTY             -                                                          DEATH            .', 'First Middlesex jury, before Mr. Recorder.']